### 6.3 Interaction Patterns

**Card Selection:**
- Hover: Subtle lift and shadow
- Click: Expands to show full details
- Selected: Colored border and "Selected" badge
- Deselect: Click X on badge

**Slider Interactions:**
- Drag thumb to position character
- Click track to jump to position
- Numbers show position (1-10)
- Color changes: Green â†’ Yellow â†’ Red

**AI Analysis:**
- Loading: "Analyzing moral dimensions..."
- Results: Expandable sections
- Suggestions: Clickable to apply
- Dismiss: Can close and recall later

### 6.4 Responsive Behavior

**Desktop (>1024px):**
- 3x2 grid for conflict cards
- Side-by-side complexity options
- Full mapping tool with controls

**Tablet (768px-1024px):**
- 2x3 grid for conflict cards
- Stacked complexity options
- Simplified mapping tool

**Mobile (<768px):**
- 1x6 vertical card list
- Single-column complexity selection
- Text-based positioning (no sliders)
- Simplified moral spectrum

### 6.5 Accessibility

**Keyboard Navigation:**
- Tab through conflict cards
- Enter to select/expand
- Arrow keys for sliders
- Escape to close modals

**Screen Reader:**
- ARIA labels for all conflicts
- Slider values announced
- Position descriptions
- Complexity explanations

**Visual Accessibility:**
- High contrast mode for spectrum
- Text labels in addition to colors
- Pattern fills for colorblind users
- Minimum 4.5:1 contrast ratio

